OL,3,CDisabled traveller left 'housebound'
OL,4,Cafter wheelchair damaged on flight
OL,6,FA disabled traveller whose #2,700
OL,7,Fwheelchair was broken on an Aer Lingus
OL,8,Fflight has said they were left
OL,9,F"housebound" for months and forced to
OL,10,Fspend their life savings on taxis and
OL,11,Ffood deliveries after the airline
OL,12,Frefused repayment.
OL,14,FWinter Mraz, 36, head of design at
OL,15,Fcraft supplies company Sophie &
OL,16,FToffee, from Liverpool, noticed their
OL,17,Fpower chair was bent and making a
OL,18,F"squeaky-grinding" sound after
OL,19,Ftravelling more than 20 hours from
OL,20,FPhoenix, Arizona, to Manchester on
OL,21,FApril 3.
